<h1>About Me</h1>

<p>
I am a disability rights practitioner working on inclusive education, accessibility,
and dignity for persons with disabilities. For several years, I have worked closely
with children with disabilities, families, schools, hospitals, and government systems
to build more inclusive environments.
</p>

<p>
I currently serve as the Executive Director of ASTHA, where we run resource centres,
inclusive education programs, trainings, and partnerships to support children and
young adults with disabilities.
</p>

<p>
Alongside my professional work, I also live with chronic pain. Through my initiative
Blooming in Pain, I write and speak about pain, identity, vulnerability, and leadership.
</p>

<p>
My work sits at the intersection of disability, pain, systems, and human dignity.
</p>

